    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "8. The UNITS given in this manual are primarily expressed as SI UNITS (International System of Unit), and alternatively expressed in the metric system and in the imperial system.\n\"Example\"\nTightening torque:\n59 - 78 N\u00b7m (6.0 - 8.0 kg-m, 43 - 58 ft-lb)",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "9. TROUBLE DIAGNOSES are included in sections dealing with complicated components.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "10. SERVICE DATA AND SPECIFICATIONS are contained at the end of each section for quick reference of data.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "11. The captions WARNING and CAUTION warn you of steps that must be followed to prevent personal injury and/or damage to some part of the vehicle.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "WARNING indicates the possibility of personal injury if instructions are not followed.",
      "style": "warning"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "CAUTION indicates the possibility of component damage if instructions are not followed.",
      "style": "caution"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "BOLD TYPED STATEMENTS except WARNING and CAUTION give you helpful information.",
      "style": "important"
    }
